PGE, Polish Utility, May Invest $3.08 Billion a Year, CEO Tells Parkiet

-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 
2011-09-29T05:39:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/pge-polish-utility-may-invest-3-08-billion-a-year-ceo-tells-parkiet.html
PGE SA, Poland’s largest utility,
will increase investment plans in a new strategy to be ready in
“several weeks” and may spend as much as 10 billion zloty
($3.05 billion) a year in 2013 to 2015, Parkiet reported, citing
Chief Executive Officer  Tomasz Zadroga .  The company is interested in buying a rival in a
neighboring country, the newspaper said, citing Zadroga.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maciej Martewicz at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net  